g.id: Using instances from training set to make predictions
Predicting is computationally intensive. O(n^2) per prediction.
For each test instance: 1. Sort n train instances by Euclidean Distance Sorting: O(n^2)
For each test instance: 2. Select top k train instances from sorted training set and average their labels.
Done! No computational work in training process.
sorted by distance from test instance
When repeated for all instances: Overall: O(n^2) * O(n) = O(n^3)
